        "positionInChapter": 0,
        "title": "Second Disaster",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Second Disaster comes approximately at the middle of Act 2, roughly 50% of the way into your story. Your lead Character has spent the first half of Act 2 trying to achieve their Storygoal, but they've been pursuing a path that won't work. The Second Disaster is a bad thing that happens at the midpoint of the story that forces your Character to try a new approach. This new approach will actually work. As an example, in the original Star Wars movie, Obi-Wan Kenobi is killed by Darth Vader at the midpoint of the story. Up till now, Luke has been following Obi-Wan and just doing what he says. Now he has to step up and start making his own decisions--and he needs to actually start using the Force. He will never win unless he becomes strong in the Force, and he has the second half of Act 2 to get strong."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
